ABC Radio National (Australian Broadcasting Corporation)
The first part of the 5th Assessment Report of the Intergovernmental Panel on Climate Change will be released in Stockholm, Sweden, later today.
There have already been several leaks from the report, including that scientists are now 95% certain of the human fingerprint in climate change.
It's also understood that the report predicts that without cuts to emissions - the world will cross the threshold of dangerous climate change in a quarter of a century.